			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I eluded to this point in a reply to another rant, but I feel this topic deserves it's own post and title and hopefully some further insight and opinions...
<br />

<br />
My biggest gripe with PoP is with the people who kite in the PoP zones. This complaint applies to 2 or 3 classes really, dr00ds, wizzys and occasionally bards also. Mind you, my main for a year and a half was a bard, and if you know anything about bards, they are quite prolific kiters on par with dr00ds and Wizzys.  With the way SOE put the PoP mobs on "the juice", I wouldn't dream of kiting with my bard in any PoP zone.  There are simply too many chances for things to go wrong and detrimentally affect innocent by-standers.
<br />

<br />
Not only is kiting greedy and very anti-social in my opinion, but for every one person who can moderately kite in the PoP zones, there are 4 idiots who canNOT handle their kiting. These idiots inevitably spill their out-of-control kite (which by that time is a full blown train) on to unsuspecting normal experience groups. I believe kiting should be outlawed in PoP zones period.
<br />

<br />
I would love to see the mechanics of mobs tinkered with so that kite classes can't enjoy their typical/comfortable kiting mechanics on the PoP mobs. Let's face it, SOE stated that they intended people to group in PoP and not solo in the PoP zones. I'd like to see mobs summon kiters. That would stop that nonsense once and for all.
<br />

<br />
There, I feel better now =P
<br />
Just my cheap 2cp
<br />

<br />
Skratchen Myitchin
<br />
59 Vah Shir Animist</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
