It's true, I can't see inside everyone's mind to confirm all them being greedy.  My perception of greed in quad kiters originated in my days as bard that single kited Wyverns in CS.  
<br />

<br />
As a bard, I had the ability at my disposal to swarm kite the whole darn zone if I had wanted to.  But I never did.  I chose to single kite one mob in a tight circle or just fear kite a mob to work on weapons skill ups.  I did this over and over again.  I was the minority here however.  I have never seen a druid or wizard kite a single mob rather than quad 4 at a time not caring if those who were single pulling had anything left to pull.  
<br />

