			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kiting, as a concept and as a method of playing is, in my mind, acceptable.  It's a awefully big risk getting four nasty monsters mad at you, getting more than 2 is usually a knock on death's door for me.
<br />

<br />
It's the way that the classes are implimented and the way that many people view the ability that causes it to be such a pain in the arse so very often.
<br />

<br />
1) All three kiting classes have a method of escape.  Wizards and Druids have evac, Bards have Selo's.  Though I don't doubt that it's difficult to get an evac off when the s**t hits the fan, there's still that level of security that goes with it
<br />
2) Quad/Swarm kiting is and always has been FAR more effective in gaining exp/loot than grouping... when it is done correctly, of course.
<br />
3) There is no penalty for screwing someone else over besides pissing the player off.
<br />

<br />
Thusly, a very large number of people whom see playing games as a way to assert their inflated ego chose the kiting method (And do NOT think I'm calling kiters egotistical bastards, I know -many- druids/wizards/bards that can kite very effectively and are wonderful people, just that the careless, rude people are far more likely to chose a kiting class for the above 3 reasons).
<br />
It is very possible and very easy for kiters to respect other people in a zone by either taking their kite somewhere else or using a different zone.  But it's also far too easy for them to not give a damn and even KS their pulls too and then purposefully run a train into their camp to get them annoyed enough to leave.
<br />

<br />
As it stands there's no possible way to 'get back' at rude and self-centered kiters (Again, not all kiters are like this) other than black-listing them, which usually does no good since the majority of these rude kiters don't go any further than is far enough to obtain phat lewt to sell and twink their other characters which no one can tell the difference between.
<br />

<br />
/kicks the dead horse's dead grandchildren's long ago crumbled and faded gravestone.<br />_________________<br /><IMG SRC="http://myweb.cableone.net/pojodan/KitchiSig2.jpg">
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543215" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543215</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
